10

The following four odes treat of love and good cheer in contrast to the serious tone of most of the other odes of the book.

These eight verses addressed to a beautiful boy, Ligurinus (4, 1, 33), warn him that beauty fades and soon he will repent his present hau'ghti· ness. The subject may have been suggested to Horace by certain Greek epigrams. Cf. Anile. Pal. 12, 35. 186. Mene, 54.
